The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 09 December is 9,838 (1,138.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 04 December, there were 526 new confirmed cases (60.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 27 November, there were 546 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 4% (20 fewer cases).
